HEADWORD: Invulgar
<hw>In*vul"gar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>vulgar</ets>.]</ety> <def>To cause to become or
appear vulgar.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Daniel.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Invulgar</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Invulgar
<hw>In*vul"gar</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>in-</ets> not +
<ets>vulgar</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not vulgar; refined; elegant.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Drayton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Invulnerability</ent>⟦br⟧
